1
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,759
Hey, boss, how much for these conches?

2
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:58,920
Tang Yi!

3
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:03,240
Tang Yi, aren't you working today?

4
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:04,920
Why didn't the handsome guy come?

5
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:06,200
Did you two have a fight?

6
00:01:06,319 --> 00:01:07,560
Why do you have so many questions?

7
00:01:07,719 --> 00:01:09,200
Which one should I answer first?

8
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:11,200
Look what I brought you.

9
00:01:11,439 --> 00:01:12,439
A teddy bear!

10
00:01:12,879 --> 00:01:13,400
Do you like it?

11
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:14,079
I love it!

12
00:01:14,439 --> 00:01:15,200
Tang Yi,

13
00:01:15,519 --> 00:01:16,640
while you were away,

14
00:01:16,879 --> 00:01:18,719
I brushed my teeth every single day.

15
00:01:18,879 --> 00:01:19,719
That's amazing!

16
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:21,040
On Pei Xi's livestream,

17
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:22,920
I learned so much about dental health.

18
00:01:23,239 --> 00:01:25,200
I want to be a doctor when I grow up.

19
00:01:25,359 --> 00:01:25,959
That way,

20
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:27,920
I can see you every day, Tang Yi!

21
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,760
You're such a sweetheart.

22
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,000
By the way, how are your eyes healing up?

23
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:32,920
Any discomfort?

24
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:33,719
No, not at all.

25
00:01:33,879 --> 00:01:35,239
My eyes are doing great.

26
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:37,239
Daddy said I should always remember

27
00:01:37,519 --> 00:01:39,319
the person who donated their cornea to me.

28
00:01:39,599 --> 00:01:41,920
When I grow up, I want to help others too.

29
00:01:42,879 --> 00:01:43,680
By the way, sweetie,

30
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:45,480
can you answer one question for me?

31
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:46,680
Of course!

32
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:48,760
Have you ever been to Pingjin with Daddy?

33
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:49,599
Yes, I have.

34
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:50,879
I went with Daddy to pick up supplies.

35
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:53,239
Look, I even fell and lost a tooth!

36
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:55,799
A doctor took me to the hospital.

37
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:57,879
That doctor was really stern,

38
00:01:58,439 --> 00:02:00,719
but his hands were big and warm,

39
00:02:01,159 --> 00:02:02,400
just like yours, Tang Yi.

40
00:02:03,079 --> 00:02:03,840
Dr. Tang.

41
00:02:04,599 --> 00:02:05,560
What brings you here?

42
00:02:06,079 --> 00:02:06,840
Master Zhou.

43
00:02:06,959 --> 00:02:07,599
Daddy!

44
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,759
Look, this is what Tang Yi

45
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,120
gave me as a gift.

46
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,280
Dr. Tang,

47
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,360
if you have something to say,

48
00:02:15,719 --> 00:02:16,960
let's talk over there.

49
00:02:24,599 --> 00:02:25,479
Master Zhou,

50
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:33,800
that's not really what happened, is it?

51
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,120
Dr. Tang,

52
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:41,639
I know you're a good person,

53
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,039
and I know about you and Dr. Jiang.

54
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,360
But you're you, and he's him.

55
00:02:46,879 --> 00:02:48,159
You don't need to defend him.

56
00:02:49,159 --> 00:02:49,960
Master Zhou,

57
00:02:50,639 --> 00:02:51,360
none of us believe

58
00:02:51,439 --> 00:02:52,840
he would do something like that.

59
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,080
If there's been a misunderstanding,

60
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,400
we can clear it up.

61
00:02:56,039 --> 00:02:56,879
But these rumors

62
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:58,680
will truly destroy his career.

63
00:02:59,919 --> 00:03:01,120
There's no misunderstanding.

64
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,840
What you saw is the truth.

65
00:03:03,759 --> 00:03:05,439
To save that rich person first,

66
00:03:05,759 --> 00:03:07,039
he abandoned my daughter.

67
00:03:07,319 --> 00:03:08,000
What gave him the right?

68
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:09,560
My daughter was so badly hurt,

69
00:03:09,759 --> 00:03:10,560
her face covered in blood,

70
00:03:10,719 --> 00:03:11,919
crying out in pain.

71
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:14,000
I begged him over and over,

72
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,080
but what did he do?

73
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:17,199
He's a cold-blooded, heartless scumbag.

74
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,520
He doesn't deserve to be a doctor.

75
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,599
But do you know what?

76
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:24,000
This "scumbag" you speak of,

77
00:03:24,759 --> 00:03:26,520
he picked up a scalpel at twenty.

78
00:03:26,919 --> 00:03:28,039
In Pingjin First Hospital's history,

79
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:29,840
he's the youngest attending physician.

80
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,759
He can work 24 hours straight,

81
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:33,080
performing eight major surgeries.

82
00:03:33,319 --> 00:03:34,199
He'll fight tooth and nail

83
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,360
for total strangers,

84
00:03:35,439 --> 00:03:37,240
standing up to renowned experts,

85
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,280
just for that one percent chance of a cure.

86
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,199
How could a person like that ever

87
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:43,120
treat patients differently based on status?

88
00:03:43,599 --> 00:03:44,520
I apologize to you.

89
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:55,199
It really was my fault back then.

90
00:03:55,759 --> 00:03:57,000
Your daughter's surgery afterwards

91
00:03:57,039 --> 00:03:58,039
was completed successfully.

92
00:03:58,520 --> 00:03:59,680
But my attitude was poor.

93
00:03:59,759 --> 00:04:00,960
I didn't explain things clearly.

94
00:04:01,479 --> 00:04:02,280
That was my fault.

95
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:03,879
Dr. Jiang.

96
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:05,439
This one next door is Director Qin's friend.

97
00:04:05,599 --> 00:04:06,240
Come handle him first.

98
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:08,319
If vital signs are stable, send for a CT scan first.

99
00:04:08,479 --> 00:04:09,680
Full scan of head, neck, chest, and abdomen.

100
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,439
Isn't there a doctor right here?

101
00:04:12,759 --> 00:04:13,840
Doctor, hurry, hurry!

102
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:14,919
The patient is undergoing debridement.

103
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,279
Who let her pull open the curtain?

104
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,480
I'm a friend of your Director Qin.

105
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:20,519
My son is badly injured.

106
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,120
I want you to examine him first.

107
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:23,279
Mom.

108
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,240
I'm so thirsty.

109
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,800
There's blood inside the helmet visor.

110
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:30,240
But no open wounds visible on the face.

111
00:04:30,319 --> 00:04:32,240
There may be intraoral injuries.

112
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:33,839
Don't remove the helmet.

113
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:42,680
What's the oxygen saturation?

114
00:04:43,399 --> 00:04:44,439
Oxygen saturation is 88.

115
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,319
Open a third IV line. Prep for surgery.

116
00:04:53,519 --> 00:04:54,199
Got it.

117
00:04:55,639 --> 00:04:56,399
Doctor.

118
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:58,040
My daughter came in first.

119
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:00,839
Her internal injuries haven't been checked yet, I...

120
00:05:02,079 --> 00:05:02,879
What are you doing?

121
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,000
You, take over the debridement.

122
00:05:05,079 --> 00:05:05,600
Okay.

123
00:05:06,279 --> 00:05:07,079
Hurry, doctor!

124
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,319
The reason I saved that person first

125
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:09,680
is because I judged

126
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:11,319
that your daughter's condition was temporarily stable.

127
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:13,439
But if that person didn't get immediate surgery,

128
00:05:14,279 --> 00:05:15,720
his life would have ended.

129
00:05:18,279 --> 00:05:20,000
I know that no matter what I say now,

130
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:21,720
it can't make up for

131
00:05:21,959 --> 00:05:23,639
the pain your daughter suffered then.

132
00:05:24,319 --> 00:05:25,519
But this is the truth.

133
00:05:26,959 --> 00:05:28,000
In a doctor's eyes,

134
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:30,160
patients aren't judged by wealth or status.

135
00:05:30,839 --> 00:05:31,720
Every life

136
00:05:32,519 --> 00:05:33,279
we treat with respect.

137
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,560
I actually...

138
00:05:45,439 --> 00:05:47,319
I'm the one who wronged you, Dr. Jiang.

139
00:05:48,439 --> 00:05:49,839
I know you're a good person too.

140
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,639
I really didn't mean to hurt you.

141
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,399
I was just so angry back then.

142
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:56,360
Furious that my daughter had to suffer so much.

143
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,759
I never thought things would turn out like this.

144
00:05:58,959 --> 00:06:01,040
Later, I wanted to come forward and explain for you.

145
00:06:02,839 --> 00:06:03,759
But I...

146
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:06,040
But after I saw those donations,

147
00:06:08,279 --> 00:06:10,399
I really had no choice.

148
00:06:12,439 --> 00:06:14,360
My mother was lying in the Intensive Care Unit.

149
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,959
Costing several thousand a day.

150
00:06:18,199 --> 00:06:20,160
And my daughter had lost her sight.

151
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:24,279
I really had nowhere left to turn.

152
00:06:28,439 --> 00:06:29,240
That money...

153
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,519
I shouldn't have taken that money.

154
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,519
I shouldn't have taken it. Don't do this.

155
00:06:33,639 --> 00:06:35,560
I'm the one who wronged you, Dr. Jiang. Master Zhou.

156
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:36,839
I'm too ashamed to face you.

157
00:06:36,879 --> 00:06:37,959
Please get up, Master Zhou. I'm sorry.

158
00:06:38,279 --> 00:06:40,360
My brother found who was behind that news story.

159
00:06:40,519 --> 00:06:41,959
Get up first, then we'll talk.

160
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:42,480
You should thank me

161
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:44,040
for not exposing what you did.

162
00:06:44,319 --> 00:06:45,160
Master Zhou, please get up.

163
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:47,040
I'm so sorry, Dr. Jiang.

164
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,240
Suit yourself.

165
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:49,800
It doesn't matter anymore.

166
00:06:55,959 --> 00:06:56,600
Get up, quickly.

167
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,839
I'm so sorry. Get up.

168
00:08:00,279 --> 00:08:01,600
You're just going to leave like this?

169
00:08:08,079 --> 00:08:08,920
What else should I do?

170
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,000
Wait around for you, the winner,

171
00:08:11,399 --> 00:08:12,279
to come laugh at me?

172
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:15,560
It's all in the past now.

173
00:08:16,519 --> 00:08:17,959
No one's going to dig up the truth.

174
00:08:19,839 --> 00:08:21,480
You don't need to use your medical family

175
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,639
and golden child halo to show me pity.

176
00:08:24,199 --> 00:08:25,439
What I, Chen Pei'ang, have done,

177
00:08:26,399 --> 00:08:27,040
I own it.

178
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:29,199
All because of Tang Yi?

179
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:34,360
Maybe.

180
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,120
Before you showed up,

181
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:39,840
I thought I'd be the one

182
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,559
who'd stay with her till the end.

183
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:45,279
But reality is just that cruel.

184
00:08:47,159 --> 00:08:48,159
You, so effortlessly,

185
00:08:49,159 --> 00:08:50,679
took away everything I had.

186
00:08:53,159 --> 00:08:54,399
She's her own person.

187
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,440
She doesn't belong to anyone.

188
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:59,879
Who she wants to be with

189
00:09:00,159 --> 00:09:01,200
is her choice.

190
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:03,600
We competed fairly.

191
00:09:06,039 --> 00:09:06,799
Fairly?

192
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:10,600
Fairly?

193
00:09:12,519 --> 00:09:13,360
Is it really fair?

194
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,399
Is it really fair?

195
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,039
People like you,

196
00:09:19,879 --> 00:09:21,440
are born at the peak,

197
00:09:23,159 --> 00:09:24,759
enjoying the best resources,

198
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,799
basking in everyone's admiration.

199
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:28,919
And me?

200
00:09:30,159 --> 00:09:32,200
I gave everything I had,

201
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,440
and the finish line I struggled to reach,

202
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:37,120
is just your starting point.

203
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,159
Do you know what having nothing means?

204
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,960
Do you know what "A slow sparrow should make an early start" means?

205
00:09:46,159 --> 00:09:47,399
Have you ever seen your parents at 3 AM,

206
00:09:47,519 --> 00:09:47,960
backs hunched over,

207
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:50,120
pedaling a tricycle to sell vegetables?

208
00:09:51,039 --> 00:09:52,679
Have you seen your siblings groveling,

209
00:09:52,799 --> 00:09:54,919
swallowing their pride to beg for loans?

210
00:09:55,279 --> 00:09:56,279
Have you spent eight straight years,

211
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:57,399
sleeping only three hours a night,

212
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:59,120
hiding under the blanket in the dorm,

213
00:09:59,159 --> 00:10:00,840
reading with a flashlight in the middle of the night?

214
00:10:01,039 --> 00:10:02,000
You haven't.

215
00:10:03,279 --> 00:10:04,600
You'll never understand.

216
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:07,279
Because you were born with everything.

217
00:10:16,759 --> 00:10:17,360
Yes.

218
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:19,639
I admit it.

219
00:10:21,519 --> 00:10:22,399
I'm jealous of you.

220
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,720
I'm insanely jealous.

221
00:10:26,639 --> 00:10:27,519
I have no family background,

222
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,559
no connections, no network.

223
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:31,679
At my lowest point,

224
00:10:31,799 --> 00:10:33,960
I had to split one cup of noodles into two meals.

225
00:10:35,639 --> 00:10:37,120
I've struggled this hard for so long

226
00:10:38,279 --> 00:10:39,720
just so I could say goodbye

227
00:10:39,879 --> 00:10:40,559
to my old life.

228
00:10:40,879 --> 00:10:42,679
Just so everyone I care about

229
00:10:42,799 --> 00:10:44,360
could live a little better.

230
00:10:44,559 --> 00:10:46,159
Just so I could stand a bit taller

231
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:47,639
in front of the person I love.

232
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:49,600
Is that so wrong? Is it?

233
00:10:54,039 --> 00:10:54,759
Why?

234
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:59,159
Why can't I even be left

235
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,600
with this tiny bit of hope?

236
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:05,519
I...

237
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,600
I never thought you were beneath me.

238
00:11:11,399 --> 00:11:13,000
And I never thought I was above anyone.

239
00:11:14,519 --> 00:11:15,919
In fact, if I were in your position,

240
00:11:16,039 --> 00:11:16,679
I might

241
00:11:17,279 --> 00:11:18,279
not have done as well as you.

242
00:11:23,679 --> 00:11:24,759
You have everything.

243
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,279
Nothing to worry about.

244
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:29,840
Of course you can sit there

245
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,080
and say all these noble things.

246
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:33,519
You only see the halo

247
00:11:33,639 --> 00:11:35,080
of a golden child above my head.

248
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:37,039
But you don't see

249
00:11:37,759 --> 00:11:39,440
how cautiously I live every single day.

250
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,879
Just because my father is Jiang Zhaohe,

251
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,200
from the moment I was born,

252
00:11:44,279 --> 00:11:45,919
I was destined to follow in his footsteps.

253
00:11:49,039 --> 00:11:50,559
I never had a carefree childhood like yours,

254
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:52,720
nor the right to choose my own interests,

255
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,320
not even the company

256
00:11:54,399 --> 00:11:55,759
of family or siblings.

257
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,440
I have no time of my own.

258
00:11:58,240 --> 00:11:59,480
And everything I do

259
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,480
is simply to be worthy

260
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:04,960
of being Jiang Zhaohe's son.

261
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:09,639
Every single day,

262
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:11,720
I'm careful,

263
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:15,120
working tirelessly, walking on thin ice.

264
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,480
I'm terrified of making the slightest mistake.

265
00:12:18,159 --> 00:12:18,919
Because if I do,

266
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,679
my colleagues will think I got in through connections,

267
00:12:21,039 --> 00:12:22,200
through the back door.

268
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,360
You think I'm not exhausted?

269
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:25,720
You think I don't feel

270
00:12:25,799 --> 00:12:27,399
suffocated and miserable too?

271
00:12:36,799 --> 00:12:38,480
I can't choose where I came from,

272
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,799
but I know how to navigate my future.

273
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:44,639
I do this

274
00:12:46,159 --> 00:12:47,679
not to prove myself to anyone,

275
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:49,919
but so I won't have regrets.

276
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:52,440
What about you?

277
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,360
All your years of hard work,

278
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:58,039
just to surpass me?

279
00:12:58,919 --> 00:13:00,919
There are countless people better than me.

280
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,320
Are you going to spend every day

281
00:13:02,399 --> 00:13:03,879
living in comparison with them,

282
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:05,399
trying to surpass each one?

283
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,080
Believe me or not,

284
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,039
but I never saw you as a rival.

285
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:20,519
Everyone has their own path,

286
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:23,000
and all I need to do

287
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:24,519
is be better than I was yesterday.

288
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,240
That's enough.

289
00:13:29,799 --> 00:13:30,679
My own path...

290
00:13:35,879 --> 00:13:37,039
I used to think

291
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:39,279
that as long as

292
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,399
I had passion in my heart,

293
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:45,120
I could definitely help more people.

294
00:13:47,919 --> 00:13:48,759
But the reality?

295
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:51,600
The reality is, no matter how hard I try,

296
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:54,159
I can't change that

297
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,960
deep-rooted prejudice and discrimination.

298
00:13:57,279 --> 00:13:58,360
Eight years studying my field,

299
00:13:59,759 --> 00:14:01,120
over a decade honing my skills,

300
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:04,320
and in the end, to others,

301
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,000
I'm less credible than

302
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,240
a plan a machine generates in three seconds.

303
00:14:11,399 --> 00:14:12,799
What am I, Chen Pei'ang, really?

304
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:15,559
I'm nothing.

305
00:14:15,879 --> 00:14:16,440
If everyone

306
00:14:16,519 --> 00:14:18,000
ran away like you do,

307
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:20,039
how would our profession ever develop?

308
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:25,159
You think just the two of us

309
00:14:26,559 --> 00:14:28,480
can change the ecosystem of this industry?

310
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:38,279
How will we know if we don't try?

311
00:14:56,559 --> 00:14:57,679
Toothaches are just from internal heat.

312
00:14:58,159 --> 00:14:59,159
Well, that's not always the case.

313
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:00,360
Dietary irritation,

314
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:01,639
poor oral hygiene,

315
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:03,120
excessive heart or liver fire,

316
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:03,960
oral infection...

317
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:05,600
all of these can cause toothaches.

318
00:15:05,759 --> 00:15:07,679
If your toothache persists

319
00:15:07,799 --> 00:15:09,039
or the symptoms get worse,

320
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,120
make sure to see a dentist promptly.

321
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:11,200
Don't put it off,

322
00:15:11,279 --> 00:15:12,879
or a small problem could turn into a big one.

